jodd.util.cl

Class ExtendedURLClassLoader

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.ClassLoader
      • java.security.SecureClassLoader
        • java.net.URLClassLoader
          • jodd.util.cl.ExtendedURLClassLoader
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Closeable, java.lang.AutoCloseable

    public class ExtendedURLClassLoader
extends java.net.URLClassLoader
    Class loader that offers two loading strategies: parent-first and parent-last. The strategy defines the class loading order between this classloader and parent class loader; i.e. defines the first class loader to be used for loading classes. Extends URLClassLoader to provide just minimal set of modifications.

    Either way, you can specify wildcard rules to force some behavior - like loading some package/class exclusively with specific loader. There are the following groups:

    • parent-only - classes will be loaded only with parent classloader.
    • loader-only - classes will be loaded only with this loader.
    • default - classes will be loaded as specified by strategy (no need to define).

    The order of matching is also set by loading strategy. For parent-first strategy, loader group rules will be checked first. For parent-last strategy, parent group rules will be checked first.

    By default, the list of parent-only group is populated with JavaInfo.getJrePackages() JRE packages}.

    When parent-last strategy is used, be aware how you use ClassLoaderUtil as it is designed to follow parent-first strategy. Use with caution as setting parent-last violates the class loader hierarchy.
